sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Dev as Developer
    participant Host as Host agent<br/>(OpenCode / Copilot)
    participant MCP as mcp-server
    participant LG as LangGraph<br/>(in-process)
    participant PG as Postgres<br/>(registry + ledger)

    Dev->>Host: "fix the durable model output cache"
    Host->>MCP: get_task_context(task, hints)
    MCP->>MCP: budget check (server-side cap)
    MCP->>LG: invoke state graph
    par four parallel pure-retrieval nodes
        LG->>PG: resolve_scope — alias index, then search
    and
        LG->>PG: blast_radius — calls/imports/tests edges
    and
        LG->>PG: conventions — rules/ADRs near scope
    and
        LG->>PG: similar_prior_changes — commit search
    end
    LG->>LG: synthesize (tier confidence, trim to budget)
    opt scope came back empty
        LG->>PG: ONE broadened retry
    end
    MCP->>PG: retrieval_event (approved · tokens · latency)
    MCP-->>Host: scope + blast radius + conventions,<br/>tiered, cited, budget_used
    Host->>Host: read ONLY files the tool didn't cover
    Host-->>Dev: plan / answer, with Sources

    rect rgb(250, 243, 230)
        Note over MCP,PG: crash path (guaranteed behavior)
        Host->>MCP: get_task_context(...)
        MCP--xMCP: unexpected mid-flight exception
        MCP->>PG: retrieval_event (error) + budget REFUND
        MCP-->>Host: tool error (never swallowed)
        Host->>Host: treat as KB gap — fall back to native reads
        Host-->>Dev: complete answer anyway
    end
